The Iowa Fireworks Farm, located at the New Virginia Exit 43 (next to Kum & Go) is going to donate $10 from the sale of every "1 Minute More" firework to the I-35 Booster Club. 1 Minute More is a great 48 shot aerial firework that lasts for over a minute with a variety of effects. Plus for anyone that likes the I-35 Booster Club Facebook Page and the Iowa Fireworks Farm Facebook Page, you‚Äôll receive 10% in free fireworks with any purchase!!
It's a win for everyone!!

Please remember to follow your local guidelines on the use of fireworks.

post_text: Hey ROADRUNNER fans! Do you remember seeing recently, the I35 driveway paintings that were done for Seniors only? Well, we have decided to sell them to all Roadrunner fans within the Interstate 35 school district. We are charging $30 and will come out to your house and paint a red, white and blue sign on your driveway, sidewalk or any concrete surface. We have also sprayed on wood and mats. The size is 2 1/2 by 2 1/2 feet. When requesting one of these, we do ask that you make payment before hand. We will contact you once we have received payment. Then we will ask you to mark off the spot with tape, just in case you are not present when we come. You can mail your payment and contact information to Interstate 35 Booster Club, I35 Schools, Box 79, Truro, IA 50257. If you have any questions, please contact via messenger. Below, please see examples of most recent Driveway paintings! And always, thank you for supporting the I35 Booster Club and I35 Schools.

Parade Winners of the 2019 I-35 Homecoming Parade are:

1st: 4H Ohio Future Feeders
2nd: Best Buddies
3rd: FFA

What a wonderful evening we had despite the weather! The decision to continue with the parade did not come lightly and had a lot of discussion yesterday on whether or not it was going to happen. We just wanted to say thank you to everyone for supporting our decision to continue with the homecoming parade and coming out to it. Bundle up and see you at the Homecoming Football game tonight!
-Sandy
